from time to time.

84
00:07:10,861 --> 00:07:13,421
It's a bad deal. You know,
his mom's on that crack pipe.

85
00:07:13,597 --> 00:07:17,055
He ain't got nobody else. He just
wanted to come along for the ride.

86
00:07:17,434 --> 00:07:19,095
- They're here?
- Yeah.

87
00:07:20,137 --> 00:07:23,573
Now, the little one, that's Steven...

88
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:25,332
...and the big one...

89
00:07:25,509 --> 00:07:26,601
Big Mike.

90
00:07:35,652 --> 00:07:37,244
STEVEN:
Swish!

91
00:07:39,756 --> 00:07:41,781
Big Mike! Ha-ha.

92
00:07:43,593 --> 00:07:45,026
Come on.

93
00:07:51,902 --> 00:07:53,494
Mother of God.

94
00:07:54,971 --> 00:07:57,940
<i>MAN: Steven Hamilton's paperwork
looks acceptable to me...</i>

95
00:07:58,108 --> 00:08:01,339
...and I believe he'll do fine.
But this other kid...

96
00:08:01,511 --> 00:08:03,570
- Big Mike.
- Michael Oher...

97
00:08:03,747 --> 00:08:06,181
...gives us no reason to believe that...

98
00:08:06,349 --> 00:08:09,716
...based on his records,
that he would be successful here.

99
00:08:09,886 --> 00:08:11,080
Well, how bad could it be?

100
00:08:11,254 --> 00:08:14,781
We're not exactly sure how old he is,
due to his lack of records.

101
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,950
He has a measured IQ of 80,
which is sixth percentile.

102
00:08:18,528 --> 00:08:22,794
His grade-point average
begins with zero, 0.6.

103
00:08:22,966 --> 00:08:24,900
Everyone passed him along.

104
00:08:25,068 --> 00:08:28,504
They gave him D's so they could
hand their problem off to the next school.

105
00:08:30,474 --> 00:08:31,805
He's a brave kid.

106
00:08:34,578 --> 00:08:39,106
For wanting to come here,
for wanting a quality education.

107
00:08:39,282 --> 00:08:43,776
An education denied him by
the poor quality of schools he's attended.

108
00:08:43,954 --> 00:08:47,754
Most kids with his background wouldn't
come within 200 miles of this place.

109
00:08:47,924 --> 00:08:52,884
Coach Cotton, we understand your interest
in this young man's athletic abilities.

110
00:08:53,063 --> 00:08:56,032
He wouldn't be able to play sports
until he got his grades up.

111
00:08:56,199 --> 00:08:58,292
Forget sports.

112
00:08:58,502 --> 00:08:59,992
Look at the wall.

113
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:04,368
"Christian." We either take that
seriously or we paint over it.

114
00:09:05,275 --> 00:09:08,676
You don't admit Michael Oher
because of sports.

115
00:09:08,845 --> 00:09:11,905
You admit him because
it's the right thing to do.

116
00:09:15,418 --> 00:09:17,409
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

117
00:09:57,394 --> 00:09:59,055
Class, this is Mike Oher...

118
00:09:59,229 --> 00:10:02,858
...and he's new here so I expect
you all to make him feel welcome.

119
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:05,228
Mike, just take any empty seat.

120
00:10:08,738 --> 00:10:11,798
This is a quiz based on the information...

121
00:10:11,975 --> 00:10:15,467
...you learned last year
in your science curriculum.

122
00:10:15,645 --> 00:10:18,409
Don't worry, it's not gonna be graded.

123
00:10:18,582 --> 00:10:21,312
I just wanna see how much information
we need to hit again.

124
00:10:21,484 --> 00:10:23,816
Just answer whatever you know.

125
00:10:45,709 --> 00:10:48,269
[BELL RINGS]

126
00:10:48,445 --> 00:10:49,935
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

127
00:10:50,113 --> 00:10:52,445
[GIRL LAUGHING]

128
00:10:56,186 --> 00:10:58,450
Thank you.

129
00:11:15,038 --> 00:11:18,599
- Can I leave now?
- Yeah.

130
00:11:22,579 --> 00:11:23,841
Take your book.

131
00:11:42,299 --> 00:11:44,392
WOMAN: I'm tired
of having someone always in our home.

132
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,330
I'm tired of him eating all the food.

133
00:11:46,503 --> 00:11:48,937
TONY: Look, man, you gotta be Christian
about this thing.

134
00:11:49,105 --> 00:11:51,300
WOMAN: Let somebody else
be Christian about this thing.

135
00:11:51,474 --> 00:11:54,671
TONY: Dee, come on, I can't kick him out
on the street like he's some dog.

136
00:11:54,844 --> 00:11:56,744
DEE: Let somebody else
take the responsibility.

137
00:11:56,913 --> 00:11:59,541
TONY: What, you want me to go to
Beale Street and drop him off?

138
00:11:59,716 --> 00:12:01,707
DEE: When do I have time
just to be with you?

139
00:12:01,885 --> 00:12:06,618
TONY: All right, all right. Whatever.
You win. I'll take care of it.

140
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:07,814
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

141
00:12:11,127 --> 00:12:13,561
WOMAN: I don't care if Patrick Ramsey
approved the chair.

142
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:17,166
He's an NFL quarterback,
not Martha fricking Stewart.

143
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:21,497
Because there is a difference
between Bunny Williams and a La-Z-Boy.

144
00:12:21,671 --> 00:12:24,162
<i>No, see, when MTV Cribs
comes to his house...</i>

145
00:12:24,341 --> 00:12:26,206
...he'll be showing off
his home theater.

146
00:12:26,376 --> 00:12:28,901
All I'm gonna see
is a brown Barcalounger.

147
00:12:29,079 --> 00:12:31,707
No, listen to me, I'm the designer,
my name is on it.

148
00:12:31,881 --> 00:12:35,078
Deliver what I ordered, all right?
Thank you.

149
00:12:35,251 --> 00:12:37,378
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

150
00:12:44,394 --> 00:12:45,452
Yeah!

151
00:12:48,832 --> 00:12:51,426
LEIGH ANNE: What'd I miss?
- Collins just got a dig.

152
00:12:51,601 --> 00:12:54,229
