me to do the problems on my own.

174
00:14:20,890 --> 00:14:23,290
I have never done homework in my life.

175
00:14:24,093 --> 00:14:28,860
I go to the bathroom,
look in the mirror and say:

176
00:14:29,165 --> 00:14:30,860
'This is not Michael Oher."'

177
00:14:35,738 --> 00:14:37,831
He entitled it "White Walls."

178
00:14:38,107 --> 00:14:39,972
How's the spelling?

179
00:14:48,918 --> 00:14:51,580
[CHUCKLING]

180
00:14:51,888 --> 00:14:53,355
Hi.

181
00:15:00,763 --> 00:15:04,324
Smile at them.
It lets them know you're their friend.

182
00:15:09,272 --> 00:15:10,967
You're Big Mike, right?

183
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:13,368
Well, I'm Sean.

184
00:15:13,543 --> 00:15:18,344
But everyone calls me SJ. It's for
Sean Junior. My father's name is Sean.

185
00:15:18,515 --> 00:15:22,417
Sean Tuohy? He was a basketball star
at Ole Miss, point guard.

186
00:15:22,585 --> 00:15:24,519
Now he owns like a million Taco Bells.

187
00:15:25,355 --> 00:15:27,482
[HONKING HORN]

188
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:29,853
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

189
00:15:35,131 --> 00:15:36,962
LEIGH ANNE: Who is that, SJ?
SJ: Big Mike.

190
00:15:38,868 --> 00:15:40,961
Get your feet off my dash.

191
00:15:42,038 --> 00:15:43,437
Thank you. Put on your seat belt.

192
00:15:43,606 --> 00:15:45,733
[STARTS ENGINE]

193
00:15:52,382 --> 00:15:54,077
Big Mike?

194
00:15:56,953 --> 00:16:01,151
Mike, I got a call from someone
at the police department.

195
00:16:05,028 --> 00:16:11,092
You remember a story in the papers
a while back about a man who...

196
00:16:11,301 --> 00:16:13,735
...fell off an overpass?

197
00:16:13,903 --> 00:16:16,098
No one knew who he was.

198
00:16:16,272 --> 00:16:21,073
They didn't know if he jumped or if...

199
00:16:22,111 --> 00:16:26,309
Well, anyway, he... He passed away.

200
00:16:29,652 --> 00:16:32,382
Mike, that man was your father.

201
00:16:35,658 --> 00:16:38,559
They've been looking for
somebody to notify and they...

202
00:16:38,728 --> 00:16:41,856
They found your name in our registry.

203
00:16:43,766 --> 00:16:46,326
I'm really sorry, son.

204
00:16:51,441 --> 00:16:53,432
Were you close to him?

205
00:16:57,814 --> 00:17:00,476
When's the last time you saw him?

206
00:17:05,655 --> 00:17:07,714
I don't know.

207
00:18:40,383 --> 00:18:43,113
- He knows it!
- Who knows it and what does he know?

208
00:18:43,386 --> 00:18:46,913
The material. Michael Oher.
I gave him this test verbally.

209
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:50,457
- Is that even allowed?
- A "C"? On how big a curve?

210
00:18:50,626 --> 00:18:53,527
He's been listening all along.
It's amazing what he's absorbed.

211
00:18:53,696 --> 00:18:57,757
And, trust me, he's listening to you too.
Now, his reading level is low...

212
00:18:57,934 --> 00:19:01,426
...and he's got no idea
how to learn in a classroom...

213
00:19:01,604 --> 00:19:06,507
I'm not saying he's gonna pass,
but Big Mike is not stupid.

214
00:19:06,676 --> 00:19:08,974
LEIGH ANNE: Hey. Good job.
SJ: Mama. Daddy.

215
00:19:09,145 --> 00:19:10,134
SEAN:
Good job. Hey...

216
00:19:10,313 --> 00:19:11,803
...I got a question for you.
SJ: Yeah?

217
00:19:11,981 --> 00:19:15,712
There was a little girl about two rows
back. What was her name?

218
00:19:15,885 --> 00:19:18,080
- Oh, that was Kinsey.
- Kinsey, yeah.

219
00:19:18,254 --> 00:19:20,722
I saw your little Indian feathers
get all ruffled up.

220
00:19:20,890 --> 00:19:22,084
Yeah! She is nice.

221
00:19:22,258 --> 00:19:24,226
SJ. Don't let this go to your head...

222
00:19:24,393 --> 00:19:27,191
...but I thought you were
very convincing in the role of...

223
00:19:27,363 --> 00:19:29,194
- Indian Number 3?
- Yes.

224
00:19:29,365 --> 00:19:32,766
I tried out for the chief,
but they gave it to Andy Sung.

225
00:19:32,935 --> 00:19:36,996
I can't be sure, but I think there's
some multi-cultural-bias thing working.

226
00:19:37,173 --> 00:19:39,869
Or maybe they just thought
that he'd make a better chief.

227
00:19:40,042 --> 00:19:41,839
