00:37:53,301 --> 00:37:56,464
- It's mine?
- Yes, sir.

466
00:37:57,539 --> 00:38:00,303
- What?
- Never had one before.

467
00:38:01,042 --> 00:38:02,805
What, a room to yourself?

468
00:38:03,545 --> 00:38:05,206
A bed.

469
00:38:14,589 --> 00:38:17,217
Well, you have one now.

470
00:38:48,924 --> 00:38:51,825
MRS. BOSWELL:
Okay. Define osmosis.

471
00:38:52,527 --> 00:38:54,791
I think I know that one.

472
00:38:55,497 --> 00:38:59,126
It's when water passes through
a barrier.

473
00:38:59,301 --> 00:39:01,792
That's basically right, Michael.
Very good.

474
00:39:09,577 --> 00:39:13,513
Name the combatants
in the Battle of Waterloo.

475
00:39:13,682 --> 00:39:16,412
I know that one. Um...

476
00:39:16,584 --> 00:39:18,347
- The little guy, Napoleon.
- Uh-huh.

477
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:22,513
He was on one side
and a duke was on the other.

478
00:39:22,691 --> 00:39:24,181
Duke of Wellington.

479
00:39:24,359 --> 00:39:27,419
Yeah, and the Duke of Wellington,
he had Russians helping him.

480
00:39:27,595 --> 00:39:28,619
Prussians.

481
00:39:42,877 --> 00:39:47,610
Enough with the rugby shirts.
You look like a giant bumblebee.

482
00:39:49,951 --> 00:39:51,179
SJ:
That Taco Bell.

483
00:39:51,353 --> 00:39:55,119
KFC catty-corner. And
the Long John Silver's on the next block.

484
00:39:55,290 --> 00:39:56,314
MICHAEL:
You own all of them?

485
00:39:56,491 --> 00:39:59,221
- Yeah. We've got like hundreds.
- Eighty-five.

486
00:39:59,494 --> 00:40:01,689
Is that why Mr. Tuohy
don't have to go to work?

487
00:40:01,930 --> 00:40:05,889
Whoa, whoa! Hey! I'm working even
when I'm not working.

488
00:40:06,634 --> 00:40:09,728
- What?
- And you eat at all these places for free?

489
00:40:09,904 --> 00:40:11,872
All you want. It's awesome.

490
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:14,975
What do y'all do with all
the leftover food from the restaurant?

491
00:40:15,143 --> 00:40:17,509
We have to throw some out,
what's already cooked.

492
00:40:17,679 --> 00:40:20,477
- That's too bad.
- Yeah, I'd rather sell it.

493
00:40:20,648 --> 00:40:22,980
Seems like you could give it away
or something.

494
00:40:23,151 --> 00:40:26,951
- You should check into that, Daddy.
SEAN: All right, I will, SJ.

495
00:40:27,122 --> 00:40:29,920
How come we're not eating
at one of your restaurants tonight?

496
00:40:30,091 --> 00:40:33,549
- Well, because tonight is a special occasion.
SJ: What?

497
00:40:34,095 --> 00:40:37,553
I talked to Coach Cotton. He said
Michael's grades have improved enough...

498
00:40:37,732 --> 00:40:40,565
...that he can go out
for spring football in March.

499
00:40:40,735 --> 00:40:44,102
- Isn't that great?
- Oh, man! You're gonna crush some people!

500
00:40:44,706 --> 00:40:46,435
[SEAN CHUCKLES]

501
00:40:51,446 --> 00:40:54,244
- Hey, guys, how we doing?
- Great, thank you.

502
00:40:55,116 --> 00:40:58,574
I've got a design book I need to get.
Why don't you check our reservation?

503
00:40:58,753 --> 00:41:00,653
They'll seat us right away.
Can't it wait?

504
00:41:00,822 --> 00:41:03,290
They might be closed by then.
Come on, SJ!

505
00:41:03,458 --> 00:41:04,982
I need some new magazines.

506
00:41:07,362 --> 00:41:09,262
Michael, come on. Come on.

507
00:41:20,408 --> 00:41:23,741
Collins? Collins?

508
00:41:24,212 --> 00:41:26,737
Collins, come on, your dad's
already PO'd. Let's go.

509
00:41:26,915 --> 00:41:28,109
COLLINS:
Over here.

510
00:41:29,717 --> 00:41:31,844
[COLLINS CHUCKLING]

511
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:34,113
[CHATTERING]

512
00:41:36,491 --> 00:41:41,190
You remember this one, Mom?
You read it to us like a thousand times.

513
00:41:41,596 --> 00:41:45,293
"He gnashed his terrible teeth
and he roared his terrible roar."

514
00:41:46,367 --> 00:41:48,267
I always liked this one.

515
00:41:48,436 --> 00:41:49,801
<i>Mm. Ferdinand.</i>

516
00:41:50,105 --> 00:41:51,936
Me too.

517
00:41:52,140 --> 00:41:55,632
Michael, your mama ever read
either one of those books to you?

518
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,438
No?

519
00:42:01,149 --> 00:42:02,707
COLLINS:
How cute!

520
00:42:02,884 --> 00:42:04,374
SEAN:
It was a good steak, huh?

521
00:42:04,552 --> 00:42:05,541
COLLINS:
Thank you, Daddy.

522
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:07,278
LEIGH ANNE:
Thank you for a lovely dinner, Papa.

523
00:42:07,455 --> 00:42:08,820
SEAN:
Here we go.

524
00:42:24,005 --> 00:42:25,996
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

525
00:42:44,025 --> 00:42:48,758
Michael. Who was that boy
you were talking to at the restaurant?

526
00:42:48,930 --> 00:42:50,898
Marcus.

527
00:42:51,566 --> 00:42:55,662
- Marcus, and he... He works there?
- Yeah.

528
00:42:56,771 --> 00:42:58,602
How do you know him?

529
00:43:00,141 --> 00:43:02,336
He's my brother.

530
00:43:08,883 --> 00:43:11,784
Well, we'd really... We'd really
like to meet him someday.

531
00:43:13,021 --> 00:43:15,319
Would that be okay with you?

532
00:43:15,790 --> 00:43:17,724
MICHAEL:
I don't know where he stays.

533
00:43:18,426 --> 00:43:20,917
LEIGH ANNE:
When was the last time you saw him?

534
00:43:23,765 --> 00:43:25,323
When I was little, maybe.

535
00:43:29,971 --> 00:43:34,032
<i>LEIGH ANNE: "Once upon a time in Spain,
there was a little bull...</i>

536
00:43:34,209 --> 00:43:37,372
...and his name was Ferdinand.

537
00:43:37,745 --> 00:43:41,044
All the other little bulls he lived with
would run and jump...

538
00:43:41,216 --> 00:43:43,946
...and butt their heads together.

539
00:43:44,586 --> 00:43:47,111
But not Ferdinand.

540
00:43:48,289 --> 00:43:54,091
He liked to sit just quietly
and smell the flowers.

541
00:43:55,196 --> 00:43:58,996
He had a favorite spot out
in the pasture under a cork tree.

542
00:44:00,602 --> 00:44:02,729
<i>LEIGH ANNE:
It was his favorite tree...</i>

543
00:44:02,904 --> 00:44:08,467
<i>... and he would sit in its shade
all day and smell the flowers."</i>

544
00:44:08,643 --> 00:44:11,407
- Good night.
- Good night.

545
00:44:13,781 --> 00:44:16,375
- What?
- What?

546
00:44:16,651 --> 00:44:18,778
Why are you smiling?

547
00:44:19,053 --> 00:44:23,422
I don't know, I'm just happy.
Real happy.

548
00:44:23,591 --> 00:44:26,560
Does this happiness have anything
to do with Michael?

549
00:44:26,728 --> 00:44:28,355
No.

550
00:44:29,163 --> 00:44:32,064
It has everything to do with Michael.

551
00:44:33,434 --> 00:44:35,925
Mm. Mm.

552
00:44:36,170 --> 00:44:38,138
- Happy's good.
- Mm.

553
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:40,767
You know what I think we should do?

554
00:44:40,942 --> 00:44:43,740
We should start a charity
for kids like Michael.

555
00:44:43,911 --> 00:44:46,345
- Okay.
- Maybe fund a program at Wingate.

556
00:44:46,514 --> 00:44:47,538
Sure.

557
00:44:47,715 --> 00:44:49,979
Lord knows that school
could use a little color.

558
00:44:50,151 --> 00:44:53,746
Poor Michael's like a fly in the milk
in that place.

559
00:44:53,921 --> 00:44:55,821
Are you listening to me?

560
00:44:57,659 --> 00:45:02,289
- Hmm?
- I try to concentrate on one...

561
00:45:03,097 --> 00:45:04,758
...thing...

562
00:45:05,199 --> 00:45:06,860
...at a time.

563
00:45:07,035 --> 00:45:08,730
[WHISPERING]
You knew I was a multitasker...

564
00:45:08,903 --> 00:45:10,268
...when you married me, right?

565
00:45:10,438 --> 00:45:14,499
- I sure did.
- Right. Okay, just checking.

566
00:45:18,313 --> 00:45:22,682
Okay, Tuohy family.
Big smiles, everyone.

567
00:45:23,484 --> 00:45:27,386
And one, two, three!

568
00:45:29,824 --> 00:45:30,848
Michael.

569
00:45:31,025 --> 00:45:33,152
Come on down here
and get in the next one.

570
00:45:33,361 --> 00:45:36,353
Come on. Come on. Come on down.

571
00:45:41,703 --> 00:45:44,763
Oh, come on. It's not like I'm gonna
put it on the Christmas card.

572
00:45:44,939 --> 00:45:49,239
Okay, let's scootch in a little tighter.

573
00:45:49,410 --> 00:45:50,934
That's good.

574
00:45:51,713 --> 00:45:53,044
Really big smiles.

575
00:45:53,214 --> 00:45:55,876
Okay, one, two, three.

576
00:45:56,050 --> 00:45:57,847
- Say "Rebels!"
ALL: Rebels!

577
00:46:02,056 --> 00:46:04,581
<i>ANNOUNCER [ON TV]: ... a blitz off
the corner, quick pass over the middle.</i>

578
00:46:04,759 --> 00:46:09,025
<i>- The hot route was there. And that's...
LEIGH ANNE: I got it.</i>

579
00:46:09,697 --> 00:46:12,029
- Who's winning?
- Tennessee.

580
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:14,862
- Ugh. Who they playing?
- Clemson.

581
00:46:15,036 --> 00:46:17,698
Your mama roots against Tennessee
no matter who they play?

582
00:46:17,872 --> 00:46:20,306
Uh... Yes, I do. With gusto.

583
00:46:20,475 --> 00:46:22,375
She can't stand Tennessee.

584
00:46:22,543 --> 00:46:25,603
Collie-bell, I thought you were
going over to your boyfriend's.

585
00:46:25,780 --> 00:46:27,645
Thought I'd hang around here
for the day.

586
00:46:28,516 --> 00:46:29,949
Hmm.

587
00:46:30,184 --> 00:46:31,742
I like that.

588
00:46:31,919 --> 00:46:34,820
There's a couple messages on the machine.
I didn't check them.

589
00:46:34,989 --> 00:46:36,422
LEIGH ANNE:
All right.

590
00:46:37,392 --> 00:46:40,793
<i>BOBBY: Hey, Sean, hey, Leigh Anne, it's
your cousin Bobby. Happy New Year's.</i>

591
00:46:41,028 --> 00:46:43,895
- Listen, I've had about five cold ones...
- Of course you have.

592
00:46:44,065 --> 00:46:46,124
<i>... so I'm just gonna go ahead and ask:</i>

593
00:46:46,701 --> 00:46:50,034
Did y'all know there's a colored boy
in your Christmas card?

594
00:46:51,606 --> 00:46:52,732
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

595
00:46:53,074 --> 00:46:54,803
What?

596
00:46:55,410 --> 00:46:58,402
You just looked teeny-tiny next to him.

597
00:46:58,579 --> 00:47:00,547
Right? Like Jessica Lange and King Kong.

598
00:47:00,715 --> 00:47:01,773
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

599
00:47:01,949 --> 00:47:04,543
Hey, does Michael get
the family discount at Taco Bell?

600
00:47:04,719 --> 00:47:08,246
Because if he does,
Sean's gonna lose a few stores.

601
00:47:08,423 --> 00:47:09,481
He's a good kid.

602
00:47:09,657 --> 00:47:12,592
Well, I say you make it official
and just adopt him.

603
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:14,193
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

604
00:47:14,362 --> 00:47:18,662
He's gonna be 18 in a few months. Doesn't
really make much sense to legally adopt.

605
00:47:21,836 --> 00:47:22,860
Leigh Anne.

606
00:47:23,337 --> 00:47:25,862
Is this some sort of white-guilt thing?

607
00:47:26,207 --> 00:47:28,505
ELAINE:
What will your daddy say?

608
00:47:29,210 --> 00:47:32,509
Um... Before or after
he turns over in his grave?

609
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:35,148
Daddy's been gone five years, Elaine.

610
00:47:35,316 --> 00:47:38,444
Make matters worse, you were
at the funeral. Remember?

611
00:47:38,619 --> 00:47:40,985
You wore Chanel
and that awful black hat.

612
00:47:41,155 --> 00:47:42,952
Look, here's the deal.

613
00:47:43,124 --> 00:47:46,355
I don't need y'all to approve
my choices, all right?

614
00:47:46,527 --> 00:47:50,691
But I do ask that you respect them. You
have no idea what this boy's been through.

615
00:47:50,865 --> 00:47:53,527
And if this is gonna become
some running diatribe...

616
00:47:53,701 --> 00:47:56,397
...I can find an overpriced salad
a lot closer to home.

617
00:47:58,406 --> 00:48:01,773
- Leigh Anne, I'm sorry. We didn't intend to...
- No, we didn't, really.

618
00:48:01,943 --> 00:48:05,174
BETH:
I think what you're doing is so great.

619
00:48:05,346 --> 00:48:08,110
To open up your home to him?

620
00:48:08,483 --> 00:48:10,747
Honey, you're changing that boy's life.

621
00:48:11,586 --> 00:48:13,178
No.

622
00:48:13,721 --> 00:48:15,313
He's changing mine.

623
00:48:16,891 --> 00:48:19,223
And that's awesome for you,
but what about Collins?

624
00:48:21,062 --> 00:48:23,360
- What about Collins?
ELAINE: Aren't you worried?

625
00:48:23,531 --> 00:48:25,226
I mean, even just a little?

626
00:48:25,399 --> 00:48:29,836
He's a boy, a large, black boy,
sleeping under the same roof.

627
00:48:32,540 --> 00:48:33,837
Shame on you.

628
00:48:39,046 --> 00:48:40,377
I've got this.

629
00:48:42,483 --> 00:48:44,280
<i>LEIGH ANNE:
Be honest with me, okay?</i>

630
00:48:46,187 --> 00:48:49,850
Does Michael being here
make you uncomfortable?

631
00:48:50,491 --> 00:48:53,927
They're stupid kids.
Who cares what they say?

632
00:48:54,095 --> 00:48:57,258
- What kids?
- At school.

633
00:48:57,765 --> 00:48:59,096
They're juvenile.

634
00:48:59,267 --> 00:49:01,292
And what do the juvenile kids say?

635
00:49:02,370 --> 00:49:04,600
It's really not worth repeating.

636
00:49:05,740 --> 00:49:07,640
And don't worry about SJ.

637
00:49:07,942 --> 00:49:12,140
He likes all the attention. He introduces
Michael as his big brother.

638
00:49:16,851 --> 00:49:18,216
And what about you?

639
00:49:18,619 --> 00:49:20,587
It's fine.

640
00:49:22,390 --> 00:49:25,484
I mean, you can't just throw him
out on the street.

641
00:49:25,660 --> 00:49:27,821
I could make other arrangements.

642
00:49:31,832 --> 00:49:34,392
GIRL: Hi, Mike.
- Hi. Need a push?

643
00:49:34,569 --> 00:49:36,196
Yes.

644
00:49:41,275 --> 00:49:43,800
MICHAEL: Oh.
GIRL: Higher, Mike, higher!

645
00:49:43,978 --> 00:49:47,414
[MICHAEL & GIRLS CHUCKLING]

646
00:49:47,615 --> 00:49:49,606
GIRL:
Higher!

647
00:49:51,852 --> 00:49:53,342
[GIRL GIGGLING]

648
00:49:53,821 --> 00:49:55,982
Higher!

649
00:49:56,891 --> 00:49:59,325
[MICHAEL & GIRLS CHUCKLING]

650
00:49:59,660 --> 00:50:02,788
GIRL:
Don't look down, don't look down. Ah!

651
00:50:02,964 --> 00:50:03,988
[MICHAEL CHUCKLES]

652
00:50:36,030 --> 00:50:38,999
- Where are you going?
- Collins?

653
00:50:50,611 --> 00:50:52,909
Quit looking at me like that.

654
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:56,015
I mean, we study together at home.

655
00:51:12,733 --> 00:51:17,193
You know how much those things weigh?
This kid's gonna make us all famous.

656
00:51:17,371 --> 00:51:18,736
[CHUCKLES]

657
00:51:18,906 --> 00:51:23,138
Easy, Bert, man. It's only the spring.
He hasn't even had his first practice yet.

658
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:25,335
No, he's a player.

659
00:51:25,780 --> 00:51:27,270
PLAYERS:
Break!

660
00:51:27,748 --> 00:51:29,716
QB: Ready.
PLAYERS: Break!

661
00:51:30,317 --> 00:51:33,980
COTTON: Get down, son.
Get down in your stance. In your stance!

662
00:51:34,255 --> 00:51:35,279
QB:
Go!

663
00:51:36,490 --> 00:51:40,256
COTTON:
Shuck him, shuck him! Ah, ah...

664
00:51:41,328 --> 00:51:44,422
Mike, son, you...
You fought off the block...

665
00:51:44,598 --> 00:51:46,930
...but then you wanna shuck
the blocker.

666
00:51:47,101 --> 00:51:50,070
All right? Shuck him. All right, let's go.

667
00:51:50,871 --> 00:51:52,600
QB:
Huddle up.

668
00:51:52,773 --> 00:51:54,502
Papa.

669
00:51:54,675 --> 00:51:55,699
[SIGHS]

670
00:51:55,876 --> 00:51:57,275
How's he doing?

671
00:51:57,445 --> 00:51:58,969
Hasn't quite gotten the hang of it yet.

672
00:51:59,146 --> 00:52:02,547
[PLAYERS YELLING]

673
00:52:04,485 --> 00:52:06,248
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

674
00:52:07,121 --> 00:52:08,213
COTTON:
Mike, son.

675
00:52:08,389 --> 00:52:10,482
Shuck the blocker, don't tote him!

676
00:52:10,658 --> 00:52:12,592
QB:
Set, go!

677
00:52:13,994 --> 00:52:17,623
No, no, no! No, no, no!

678
00:52:18,365 --> 00:52:19,923
QB:
Set, go!

679
00:52:28,642 --> 00:52:30,439
Balloons! They're balloons!

680
00:52:31,078 --> 00:52:34,013
Guys, quit looking at the balloons.
Everybody!

681
00:52:34,181 --> 00:52:37,048
COTTON: Most kids from bad situations
can't wait to be violent...

682
00:52:37,218 --> 00:52:38,845
...and that comes out on the field.

683
00:52:39,019 --> 00:52:42,182
But this kid, he acts like
he doesn't wanna hit anyone.

684
00:52:42,356 --> 00:52:44,256
He's Ferdinand the Bull.

685
00:52:44,425 --> 00:52:46,154
COTTON: What?
- Nothing.

686
00:52:47,661 --> 00:52:52,223
I thought he was gonna be a player. I can't
believe I used up all my chips to get him in.

687
00:52:52,399 --> 00:52:54,560
I thought you said
it was your Christian duty.

688
00:52:56,270 --> 00:52:58,966
Look, Bert, he's never even played before.

689
00:53:00,040 --> 00:53:03,339
Yeah, and he won't this fall if he
doesn't improve a lot before then.

690
00:53:03,677 --> 00:53:05,542
Who died and made him Bear Bryant?

691
00:53:05,713 --> 00:53:07,078
[LAUGHS]

692
00:53:07,248 --> 00:53:08,613
Unbelievable.

693
00:53:09,750 --> 00:53:11,877
Oh, God bless me.

694
00:53:12,052 --> 00:53:13,713
This is your summer workout sheet.

695
00:53:13,888 --> 00:53:16,118
Now, first it says to warm up
and get loose.

696
00:53:17,057 --> 00:53:18,820
Well, go ahead, get loose.

697
00:53:21,695 --> 00:53:23,253
Are you loose?

698
00:53:23,631 --> 00:53:27,397
Okay. Next, it's five 100-yard runs
to stretch out your legs.

699
00:53:27,568 --> 00:53:29,832
- Can we just go home and play video games?
- Look!

700
00:53:30,004 --> 00:53:33,167
Everybody at Wingate is expecting you
to be a star football player.

701
00:53:33,340 --> 00:53:34,967
Don't wanna let them down,
do you?

702
00:53:35,142 --> 00:53:37,076
- I don't know.
- What about Dad and Mom?

703
00:53:37,244 --> 00:53:39,906
Because, you see, in our family,
everyone's an athlete.

704
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:44,141
Dad was a basketball star.
Collins plays volleyball and runs track.

705
00:53:44,318 --> 00:53:46,650
And me, well, as you know, I do it all.

706
00:53:46,821 --> 00:53:49,312
And Mom... Well, Mom was a cheerleader...

707
