psychologist or something?

752
00:56:36,190 --> 00:56:38,852
- Do you really expect Big Mike to...?
- Michael.

753
00:56:39,026 --> 00:56:40,960
Do you expect Michael
to lie on a couch...

754
00:56:41,128 --> 00:56:43,653
...and talk about his childhood
like he's Woody Allen?

755
00:56:43,831 --> 00:56:46,493
I mean, Michael's gift
is his ability to forget.

756
00:56:46,667 --> 00:56:50,626
He's mad at no one and he really
doesn't care what happened in the past.

757
00:56:51,271 --> 00:56:52,397
You're right.

758
00:56:53,107 --> 00:56:56,372
Excuse me? "You're right"?

759
00:56:56,543 --> 00:56:59,011
How'd those words taste
coming out of your mouth?

760
00:56:59,179 --> 00:57:00,612
Like vinegar.

761
00:57:09,456 --> 00:57:12,186
Well, at least promise me
you'll think about it.

762
00:57:12,359 --> 00:57:14,156
All right.

763
00:57:14,862 --> 00:57:18,229
"All right, you'll think about it,"
or, "All right, we should do it"?

764
00:57:18,399 --> 00:57:20,629
Is there a difference?

765
00:57:22,836 --> 00:57:28,103
Just tell Gerald to hold on to the chiffonier
and I will be by there after a while.

766
00:57:28,542 --> 00:57:32,376
