without even telling his mother?

795
00:59:29,429 --> 00:59:31,693
MAN 1:
Check out this piece right here.

796
00:59:31,865 --> 00:59:33,526
MAN 2: Yeah.
MAN 1: Damn, girl.

797
00:59:38,872 --> 00:59:39,861
<i>LEIGH ANNE:
Miss Oher?</i>

798
00:59:43,677 --> 00:59:46,703
Hi. Miss... Miss Oher?

799
00:59:48,448 --> 00:59:51,679
- You from the state?
- No.

800
00:59:51,885 --> 00:59:54,911
My name is Leigh Anne Tuohy,
and your son...

801
00:59:55,255 --> 00:59:58,224
...Michael, lives with me...

802
00:59:58,892 --> 01:00:00,985
...and my family.

803
01:00:07,367 --> 01:00:10,393
How is my boy? How's Big Mike?

804
01:00:10,571 --> 01:00:13,665
He's fine. He's doing real well.

805
01:00:14,408 --> 01:00:16,899
We might have some wine in the kitchen,
if you...

806
01:00:17,077 --> 01:00:19,068
Oh, no, no. That's real kind.

807
01:00:19,446 --> 01:00:21,277
When did you last see Michael?

808
01:00:22,849 --> 01:00:24,817
I don't know.

809
01:00:24,985 --> 01:00:29,149
How many...? How many foster kids
you got living with you?

810
01:00:29,323 --> 01:00:33,419
Oh, I'm not a foster parent to Michael.
We're just helping him out.

811
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:35,318
State don't pay you nothing?

812
01:00:35,629 --> 01:00:37,563
No, no.

813
01:00:37,731 --> 01:00:41,167
And you feed him and
you buy him clothes too?

814
01:00:41,335 --> 01:00:44,304
Well, when we can find them
in his size.

815
01:00:47,507 --> 01:00:49,805
You are a fine Christian lady.

816
01:00:50,177 --> 01:00:52,509
Well, I try to be.

817
01:00:53,814 --> 01:00:56,214
This all real nice, what you're doing...

818
01:00:56,383 --> 01:00:59,841
...but don't be surprised if one day
you wake up and he gone.

819
01:01:01,021 --> 01:01:02,283
What do you mean?

820
01:01:02,456 --> 01:01:07,086
He's a runner. That's what the state
called him after they took him from me.

821
01:01:09,997 --> 01:01:12,659
Every foster home they sent him to...

822
01:01:13,000 --> 01:01:16,231
...he'd slip out the window at night
and come looking for me.

823
01:01:16,403 --> 01:01:21,670
No matter where I was, that boy
would come find me, take care of me.

824
01:01:23,543 --> 01:01:27,206
I've had some health problems.

825
01:01:28,348 --> 01:01:32,444
Miss Oher, was Michael born
under a different name?

826
01:01:33,287 --> 01:01:37,280
Proctor. That was his daddy's last name.

827
01:01:37,791 --> 01:01:39,122
Where is he?

828
01:01:39,293 --> 01:01:43,127
- I ain't seen him since he left.
- And when was that?

829
01:01:43,297 --> 01:01:45,356
Week after Mike was born.

830
01:01:46,333 --> 01:01:48,392
Do you happen to have
his birth certificate?

831
01:01:56,625 --> 01:01:59,958
It's all right. I'll figure it out.

832
01:02:00,762 --> 01:02:02,161
[CLEARS THROAT]

833
01:02:14,242 --> 01:02:17,268
Mrs. Oher, you'll always be
Michael's mama.

834
01:02:21,283 --> 01:02:22,716
Would you like to see him?

835
01:02:22,884 --> 01:02:26,786
[VOICE BREAKING]
No. Not this way.

836
01:02:29,057 --> 01:02:31,321
It's Williams.

837
