LEIGH ANNE:
One more.

853
01:04:13,361 --> 01:04:15,659
One more. There you go.

854
01:04:16,731 --> 01:04:19,131
All right. Take off the blindfold.

855
01:04:23,304 --> 01:04:27,798
SEAN: Well? That's the one you wanted,
isn't it? Heh.

856
01:04:27,976 --> 01:04:31,412
Here. Here you go, go ahead.
Take it for a ride. Go on.

857
01:04:31,579 --> 01:04:34,548
SJ: Can I go too?
- Yeah, but, Michael? Be careful.

858
01:04:34,716 --> 01:04:36,707
Shotgun!

859
01:04:36,885 --> 01:04:38,352
Whoo-hoo!

860
01:04:39,487 --> 01:04:43,082
- He wanted a truck?
- Well, Michael thinks he's a redneck.

861
01:04:43,258 --> 01:04:45,192
SJ:
Come on, Michael!

862
01:04:45,794 --> 01:04:49,594
Okay. See, you're the ketchup,
here at left tackle on the weak side.

863
01:04:49,764 --> 01:04:52,699
The first play is simple. Gap.

864
01:04:54,736 --> 01:04:58,729
Now, see, this just means that you're
going to block whoever's in front of you...

865
01:04:58,907 --> 01:05:02,104
