01:06:32,133 --> 01:06:33,225
[GLASS SHATTERING]

901
01:06:33,434 --> 01:06:35,299
LEIGH ANNE:
This is not a $40,000 Oushak, Omid.

902
01:06:35,470 --> 01:06:36,494
[PHONE RINGING]

903
01:06:36,671 --> 01:06:37,763
You're crazy, Leigh Anne.

904
01:06:37,939 --> 01:06:41,170
The borders are different widths.
They've been altered.

905
01:06:41,342 --> 01:06:45,176
We'll give you 17, tops, all right? Hello.

906
01:06:45,346 --> 01:06:47,371
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

907
01:06:47,549 --> 01:06:49,073
[SIRENS WAILING]

908
01:06:49,250 --> 01:06:51,081
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Ma'am, you can't get through.

909
01:06:51,252 --> 01:06:53,652
Those are my kids. Those are my kids.

910
01:06:56,124 --> 01:06:58,388
- Oh, my God.
MICHAEL: Please, God, let him be okay.

911
01:06:58,560 --> 01:07:00,585
LEIGH ANNE: Where are they?!
MICHAEL: I'm so sorry!

912
01:07:00,762 --> 01:07:04,858
- Michael, are you okay?
- I'm fine! SJ! Go help SJ!

913
01:07:05,533 --> 01:07:08,058
I'm so sorry. So sorry.

914
01:07:08,536 --> 01:07:10,197
MAN 1:
How are his vitals?

915
01:07:10,371 --> 01:07:11,929
MAN 2: Excuse me, ma'am.
- That's my son.

916
01:07:12,106 --> 01:07:14,370
SJ. SJ, baby.

917
01:07:14,542 --> 01:07:16,169
- Mama?
- Yes, baby?

918
01:07:16,344 --> 01:07:18,710
Do you think the blood'll
come out of my shirt?

919
01:07:20,215 --> 01:07:23,548
Yes, I think the blood
will come out of your shirt.

920
01:07:23,718 --> 01:07:25,481
MAN:
An air bag deploys at 200 miles an hour.

921
01:07:25,653 --> 01:07:27,780
Your son is too small
to be in the front seat.

922
01:07:27,956 --> 01:07:29,548
But he is okay, right?

923
01:07:29,724 --> 01:07:33,524
Busted lip, bruised face. Usually when
someone his size gets hit with a air bag...

924
01:07:33,695 --> 01:07:36,220
...it's a fractured face, broken neck,
maybe worse.

925
01:07:36,397 --> 01:07:40,197
It's like the air bag was coming for him
and changed direction.

926
01:07:40,368 --> 01:07:42,529
It's probably defective or something...

927
01:07:42,704 --> 01:07:45,036
...but your son's very, very lucky.

928
01:07:45,206 --> 01:07:48,573
No, I did. I called the insurance,
it's fine. It's fine.

929
01:07:48,743 --> 01:07:50,677
I'll talk to you later. I gotta go. Bye.

930
01:07:52,347 --> 01:07:53,712
[SIGHS]

931
01:07:54,515 --> 01:07:56,676
SJ's fine.

932
01:07:57,518 --> 01:08:02,251
He is. He's actually enjoying all
the attention he's getting back there.

933
01:08:03,491 --> 01:08:07,655
Hey, Michael, could've happened to
anyone, all right? It's not your fault.

934
01:08:08,663 --> 01:08:10,597
Honey, look at me.

