Michael, up top!

1498
01:42:50,450 --> 01:42:51,474
[CHUCKLES]

1499
01:42:53,686 --> 01:42:55,153
Way to go, bro.

1500
01:42:55,822 --> 01:42:57,255
All right, that's enough.

1501
01:42:57,423 --> 01:43:00,881
Young man, I think I need a proper hug.

1502
01:43:06,366 --> 01:43:08,834
You're gonna be staying
in Deaton Hall. Where is it?

1503
01:43:09,002 --> 01:43:10,299
It's 109. It's right there.

1504
01:43:10,470 --> 01:43:14,031
You'll be on the meal plan so you'll be
eating over here in Johnson Commons.

1505
01:43:14,207 --> 01:43:16,300
Johnson Commons, all-you-can-eat
self-serve ice cream.

1506
01:43:16,476 --> 01:43:17,568
- Mm-hm.
- As much as you want?

1507
01:43:17,744 --> 01:43:18,768
[PHONE RINGS]

1508
01:43:18,945 --> 01:43:21,072
That's how Mama put on
her freshman 10.

1509
01:43:21,281 --> 01:43:22,305
[CHUCKLES]

1510
01:43:22,482 --> 01:43:25,883
- Stop it.
- Whew.

1511
01:43:26,619 --> 01:43:28,280
Hello.

1512
01:43:29,856 --> 01:43:31,323
This is Mrs. Tuohy.

1513
01:43:31,491 --> 01:43:35,791
They just wanna ask you a couple questions,
Michael. You have nothing to hide.

1514
01:43:36,596 --> 01:43:39,224
Mrs. Tuohy? Mr. Oher?
My name is Jocelyn Granger.

1515
01:43:39,399 --> 01:43:41,924
I'm the Assistant Director of
Enforcement for the NCAA.

1516
01:43:42,101 --> 01:43:43,534
Please, call me Leigh Anne.

1517
01:43:47,073 --> 01:43:48,700
So let's do this, shall we?

1518
01:43:48,875 --> 01:43:52,140
If you wouldn't mind,
I'd prefer to speak with Michael alone.

1519
01:43:52,779 --> 01:43:54,474
LEIGH ANNE:
And how long is that gonna take?

1520
01:43:54,647 --> 01:43:55,773
A while.

1521
01:43:58,184 --> 01:44:00,118
It's all right. It's okay.

1522
01:44:00,320 --> 01:44:01,912
Go on.

1523
01:44:04,591 --> 01:44:05,615
Michael.

1524
01:44:05,792 --> 01:44:09,387
Michael. I'll be waiting for you
in the lobby, all right?

1525
01:44:13,132 --> 01:44:14,326
<i>LEIGH ANNE:
I don't know, Sean.</i>

1526
01:44:14,500 --> 01:44:16,730
Just have a bad feeling about this one.

1527
01:44:16,903 --> 01:44:19,565
This woman is tough, tough, tough,
tough, tough. Hold on.

1528
01:44:20,607 --> 01:44:22,131
Hey.

1529
01:44:23,076 --> 01:44:24,976
The client wants what?

1530
01:44:25,912 --> 01:44:28,972
Were you aware that Coach Cotton
was accepting a job at Ole Miss?

1531
01:44:29,148 --> 01:44:30,172
No.

1532
01:44:30,350 --> 01:44:33,012
And that this job offer came
after you signed with them?

1533
01:44:34,254 --> 01:44:36,916
Sean Tuohy, your legal guardian,
went to Ole Miss.

1534
01:44:37,090 --> 01:44:38,114
He played basketball.

1535
01:44:38,725 --> 01:44:41,193
And Mrs. Tuohy went to Ole Miss
as well.

1536
01:44:41,361 --> 01:44:42,658
She was a cheerleader.

1537
01:44:42,829 --> 01:44:45,423
Is it safe to say that Ole Miss
is their favorite school?

1538
01:44:45,598 --> 01:44:49,967
Do they like any other universities?
What about, say, Tennessee?

1539
01:44:50,136 --> 01:44:51,626
No, they can't stand Tennessee.

1540
01:44:53,339 --> 01:44:54,465
And your tutor.

1541
01:44:54,641 --> 01:44:56,871
- Miss Sue?
- Miss Sue.

1542
01:44:57,043 --> 01:44:59,978
Miss Sue is an Ole Miss grad too.

1543
01:45:00,446 --> 01:45:03,279
Miss Sue ever try to persuade you
to attend Ole Miss?

1544
01:45:08,955 --> 01:45:12,288
Did you know that the Tuohys
make generous donations to Ole Miss?

1545
01:45:12,458 --> 01:45:15,120
That even Miss Sue makes donations?

1546
01:45:15,295 --> 01:45:17,422
That the Tuohys,
they have a condo in Oxford...

1547
01:45:17,597 --> 01:45:20,532
...so they can attend
as many athletic events as possible.

1548
01:45:20,767 --> 01:45:26,034
That in fact, both Sean and Leigh Anne
Tuohy are by our definition boosters.

1549
01:45:28,374 --> 01:45:30,171
Mr. Oher.

1550
01:45:30,476 --> 01:45:32,307
Mr. Oher.

1551
01:45:32,478 --> 01:45:35,413
Do you understand?
Do you know why I'm here?

1552
01:45:36,683 --> 01:45:38,207
To investigate?

1553
01:45:38,384 --> 01:45:41,376
Yes. To investigate.

1554
01:45:41,554 --> 01:45:45,354
I'm here to investigate
your odd... predicament.

1555
01:45:46,292 --> 01:45:50,058
Do you find it odd, your predicament?

1556
01:45:51,864 --> 01:45:53,593
Michael.

1557
01:45:54,167 --> 01:45:56,135
I don't know.

1558
01:45:57,136 --> 01:46:01,072
- Can l...? Can I leave now?
- No, you can't.

1559
01:46:02,308 --> 01:46:03,434
What do you want, ma'am?

1560
01:46:03,609 --> 01:46:06,134
- I want the facts. I need the truth.
- I didn't lie.

1561
01:46:06,312 --> 01:46:09,281
- I wanna know what you think about this.
- Think about what?!

1562
01:46:18,825 --> 01:46:23,057
The NCAA fears that
with your recruitment...

1563
01:46:23,229 --> 01:46:24,560
...a door might be opened...

1564
01:46:25,031 --> 01:46:27,124
...that boosters from schools
in the South...

1565
01:46:27,300 --> 01:46:30,292
...will become legal guardians
of young athletes without means...

1566
01:46:30,470 --> 01:46:32,870
...and funnel them to their alma maters.

1567
01:46:33,039 --> 01:46:36,236
I'm not saying I believe it.
I'm not saying I don't.

1568
01:46:36,409 --> 01:46:40,209
But there are many people involved in this
case who would argue that the Tuohys...

1569
01:46:40,380 --> 01:46:42,712
...they took you in, they clothed you...
- No.

1570
01:46:42,882 --> 01:46:45,817
...they fed you, they paid for
your private education.

1571
01:46:45,985 --> 01:46:48,886
- They bought you a car, paid for a tutor...
- No. No.

1572
01:46:49,055 --> 01:46:54,049
...all as part of a plan to ensure that you
play football for the University of Mississippi.

1573
01:47:11,644 --> 01:47:14,841
Michael? We're not finished.

1574
01:47:15,014 --> 01:47:17,539
The toile's not available,
like I told you months ago.

1575
01:47:17,717 --> 01:47:22,245
So why don't we go with the ticking?
The low nap. It's a beautiful...

1576
01:47:22,422 --> 01:47:25,653
I'll call you back. Bye.
Michael. So, what happened?

1577
01:47:25,958 --> 01:47:28,518
- Why'd you do it?
- What?

1578
01:47:28,694 --> 01:47:31,162
All along you wanted me
to go to Ole Miss.

1579
01:47:31,330 --> 01:47:33,355
Well, of course I did. We love Ole Miss.

1580
01:47:33,533 --> 01:47:35,000
- Why'd you do this for me?
- What?

1581
01:47:35,168 --> 01:47:38,433
Everything. Was it for you
or was it for me?

1582
01:47:38,604 --> 01:47:41,539
Was it so I would go to school
where you wanted?

1583
01:47:41,707 --> 01:47:43,868
Was it so I would do what you wanted?

1584
01:47:44,043 --> 01:47:46,443
- Michael, no, l...
- That's what she thinks.

1585
01:47:47,146 --> 01:47:48,374
Is she right?

1586
01:47:48,915 --> 01:47:51,315
Michael, honey, I need for you
to just listen to me.

1587
01:47:51,484 --> 01:47:53,042
Don't you dare lie to me.

1588
01:47:56,522 --> 01:47:58,046
I'm not stupid.

1589
01:47:58,224 --> 01:48:03,685
Michael? Michael, of course
you're not stupid, Michael. Mi...

1590
01:48:07,433 --> 01:48:09,128
I should've followed him.

1591
01:48:09,302 --> 01:48:11,293
You had no way of knowing
he'd disappear.

1592
01:48:14,440 --> 01:48:16,374
Was he right?

1593
01:48:16,943 --> 01:48:18,934
What he said about us?

1594
01:48:19,111 --> 01:48:20,669
Leigh Anne, be reasonable.

1595
01:48:20,847 --> 01:48:24,613
We gave clothes to a boy who had one
pair of shorts and we gave him a bed.

1596
01:48:24,784 --> 01:48:28,049
To hell with the NCAA.
I would do it again tomorrow.

1597
01:48:28,221 --> 01:48:30,712
What about all the rest of it?

1598
01:48:30,890 --> 01:48:34,485
All the stuff we did to make sure
that he got a scholarship.

1599
01:48:35,127 --> 01:48:37,152
A scholarship to Ole Miss.

1600
01:48:37,864 --> 01:48:40,424
He could go anywhere he wanted.
He knew that.

1601
01:48:40,600 --> 01:48:45,333
Oh, did he? Did you ask him?
Because I sure as hell know I never did.

1602
01:48:48,207 --> 01:48:51,574
Hey. Come here.

1603
01:48:59,685 --> 01:49:01,710
Yeah.

1604
01:49:02,054 --> 01:49:03,521
[SIGHS]

1605
01:49:08,094 --> 01:49:10,494
Am I a good person?

1606
01:49:10,663 --> 01:49:12,494
Not a joke.

1607
01:49:12,665 --> 01:49:14,860
Not rhetorical.

1608
01:49:16,536 --> 01:49:20,438
You are the best person that I know.

1609
01:49:21,707 --> 01:49:25,541
Everything you do, you do for others.

1610
01:49:27,013 --> 01:49:29,607
And why is that?

1611
01:49:31,751 --> 01:49:34,276
I have not a clue.

1612
01:49:35,121 --> 01:49:39,751
But you obviously get some sort of
sick satisfaction out of it.

1613
01:49:44,497 --> 01:49:47,261
- Sean.
- Yeah?

1614
01:49:47,533 --> 01:49:50,366
What if he never comes back?

1615
01:49:51,404 --> 01:49:53,395
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

1616
01:49:56,709 --> 01:50:00,008
Oh. Heh. Whoo!

1617
01:50:00,179 --> 01:50:04,081
Big Mike. Hey, get your ass
on in here, man.

1618
01:50:04,250 --> 01:50:06,616
- I'm looking for my mama.
- Your mama?

1619
01:50:06,786 --> 01:50:09,016
Yeah, I seen Dee Dee around.

1620
01:50:09,188 --> 01:50:11,418
As a matter of fact...

1621
01:50:11,591 --> 01:50:14,992
Oh, yeah, she usually stop by
for a taste around this time.

1622
01:50:15,394 --> 01:50:18,192
Look, I tell you what,
why don't you just come on inside?

1623
01:50:18,364 --> 01:50:23,802
I'm gonna get you a 40, we gonna chop
it up like real folk. Just until she get here.

1624
01:50:25,605 --> 01:50:28,802
Come on, now.
Ain't nobody gonna bite you, baby.

1625
01:50:37,183 --> 01:50:38,172
Hey.

1626
01:50:38,351 --> 01:50:41,548
Hey, Big Mike, go on down there
in the living room, man. Have a seat.

1627
01:50:41,721 --> 01:50:43,348
Liven this bitch up in here, y'all.

1628
01:50:43,522 --> 01:50:45,786
Give me a couple of 40s
out that refrigerator.

1629
01:50:45,958 --> 01:50:47,550
- Sit down, man.
- Big Mike, boy.

1630
01:50:47,727 --> 01:50:49,319
Damn, sure good to see you.

1631
01:50:49,562 --> 01:50:52,622
Yeah, you looking good too.
You looking fit.

1632
01:50:52,798 --> 01:50:54,390
